    long_description:
      "Mountain Trek Health Reset Retreat represents the premium tier of wellness retreat experiences in British Columbia. Located in the charming village of Ainsworth Hot Springs overlooking Kootenay Lake, the retreat combines over three decades of health programming expertise with a spectacular natural setting in the Kootenay Rockies.\n\nThe retreat operates as a fully immersive, all-inclusive health program where every element of the guest experience is designed to support lasting wellness transformation. Unlike traditional yoga retreats that focus primarily on mat practice, Mountain Trek integrates yoga into a comprehensive health reset that addresses fitness, nutrition, stress management, sleep quality, and emotional wellbeing.\n\nDaily yoga sessions are tailored to complement the physical demands of the overall program. Morning practices typically feature energizing flows that prepare the body for mountain hiking, while afternoon and evening sessions emphasize restorative and yin practices that promote recovery, flexibility, and nervous system regulation. The yoga curriculum is designed to be accessible to all experience levels, with instructors providing modifications and progressions to meet individual needs.\n\nGuided mountain hikes are a signature element of the Mountain Trek experience. Led by former park rangers with deep knowledge of the Kootenay landscape, these hikes range from moderate to challenging, taking guests through old-growth forests, alpine meadows, and along mountain ridges with panoramic views of the lake and surrounding peaks. The hiking program serves as moving meditation and cardiovascular fitness training while immersing guests in the spectacular natural environment.\n\nNutrition is elevated to an art and science at Mountain Trek. World-class chefs work alongside nutritionists to create meals that are both deeply satisfying and optimally nourishing. Every dish is designed to support the body's natural detoxification and healing processes while providing the energy needed for an active daily program. Dietary restrictions and preferences are accommodated with creativity and care.\n\nSpa and bodywork services complement the active programming. Massage therapists, kinesiologists, and other wellness practitioners provide treatments that address muscular tension, promote recovery, and enhance the body's response to the program. The nearby Ainsworth Hot Springs, a natural mineral hot spring emerging from a horseshoe-shaped cave, provides additional therapeutic benefit and a uniquely memorable soaking experience.\n\nPsychologists and wellness coaches round out the multidisciplinary team, offering individual sessions in stress management, sleep optimization, and work-life balance. This psychological support helps guests understand and address the patterns underlying chronic stress and health challenges.\n\nThe Mountain Trek lodge provides boutique accommodation with comfortable rooms, common gathering spaces, and panoramic lake and mountain views. The intimate scale of the retreat ensures personalized attention and a cohesive group dynamic among guests.\n\nWith rates starting from US $5,400 for the weeklong program, Mountain Trek positions itself as a premium investment in long-term health and vitality. The comprehensive approach means guests leave with practical tools, knowledge, and motivation to sustain positive changes long after returning home.",
