    tagline: "Oceanfront transformational learning centre on Gabriola Island since 1983",
    description:
      "The Haven is a not-for-profit Centre for Transformational Learning established in 1983 on seven acres of oceanfront and forested land on beautiful Gabriola Island, British Columbia. The centre integrates therapeutic yoga retreats with personal development programs rooted in body-centred psychotherapy, communication skills, and relational awareness. Programs like the Embodied Resilience retreat combine trauma-informed yoga therapy with somatic practices, offering participants a holistic approach to healing and growth. The Haven's unique blend of yoga, psychology, and community creates an environment where personal transformation is supported by professional facilitation and the natural beauty of the Gulf Islands. Accommodation and meals packages are available alongside tuition, creating an all-inclusive retreat experience on one of BC's most peaceful islands.",
    long_description:
      "The Haven occupies a distinctive position in British Columbia's retreat landscape, blending therapeutic depth with the contemplative qualities of a traditional yoga retreat centre. Established in 1983 on Gabriola Island, just a 20-minute ferry ride from Nanaimo on Vancouver Island, the centre has developed a reputation for programs that create lasting personal transformation through the integration of body, mind, and relationship.\n\nThe centre's seven-acre property combines oceanfront access with forested privacy, creating a natural sanctuary that supports the reflective and embodied work at the heart of Haven programming. The campus includes comfortable lodging, communal dining facilities, a professional-grade kitchen, meeting and practice spaces, and outdoor areas overlooking the Strait of Georgia.\n\nYoga programming at The Haven is distinguished by its therapeutic orientation. Rather than focusing primarily on physical fitness or athletic achievement, yoga at The Haven is practiced as a vehicle for self-awareness, emotional regulation, and healing. The Embodied Resilience retreat exemplifies this approach, integrating yoga therapy principles with trauma theory, somatic awareness practices, and mindful movement. Both active and restorative yoga practices are offered, meeting participants where they are physically and emotionally.\n\nThe Haven's broader programming draws on the Haven Model, an approach to personal development that integrates body-centred therapy, communication skills, and relational awareness. This model recognizes that personal growth happens not in isolation but in relationship with others and with one's own embodied experience. Programs range from introductory weekend workshops to extended residential intensives.\n\nFaculty at The Haven include registered yoga therapists, psychotherapists, body workers, and educators who share a commitment to integrative, person-centred practice. This multidisciplinary team creates programming that addresses the whole person rather than treating physical, emotional, and relational dimensions of wellbeing in isolation.\n\nAccommodation options range from shared dormitory-style rooms to private cabins, with meals available as part of comprehensive packages. The centre's kitchen prepares nutritious meals using local ingredients, with dietary accommodations available upon request.\n\nGabriola Island provides a gentle, arts-oriented community context for the retreat experience. Known as the Isle of the Arts, Gabriola hosts a thriving creative community with galleries, studios, and cultural events throughout the year. The island's beaches, hiking trails, and distinctive sandstone galleries carved by waves provide beautiful settings for walking meditation and nature connection.\n\nThe Haven's not-for-profit structure reflects its founding commitment to making transformational learning accessible. Scholarship funds and sliding-scale pricing are available for some programs, ensuring that financial constraints do not prevent motivated individuals from participating.\n\nProgram investment varies by offering, with tuition for yoga retreats starting around $495 plus accommodation and meals. Some programs bundle all costs into a single inclusive rate. The centre's registration team assists prospective participants in understanding total costs and available financial support options.",
