    tagline: "West Coast surf town yoga and wellness retreats amid old-growth rainforest and ocean waves",
    description:
      "Tofino Yoga has been welcoming retreat seekers to the wild west coast of Vancouver Island since 2014, delivering yoga teacher training, beach yoga immersions, private sessions, and curated wellness retreats against the stunning backdrop of Pacific Rim National Park Reserve. With over 25 years of accumulated teaching expertise, the team collaborates with Tofino's vibrant wellness and adventure community to create unique retreat experiences that combine yoga practice with surfing, forest bathing, and coastal exploration. The studio at 1180 Pacific Rim Highway serves as home base for programs that take practitioners from indoor studio practice to outdoor sessions on the area's renowned long-sand beaches. Tofino's position between ancient temperate rainforest and the open Pacific Ocean creates an environment of raw natural beauty that amplifies the transformative potential of retreat practice.",
    long_description:
      "Tofino Yoga captures the wild, soulful essence of one of Canada's most iconic coastal destinations and channels it into yoga and wellness experiences that are uniquely west coast. Located on the Pacific Rim Highway in Tofino, the westernmost town on Vancouver Island, the studio and retreat operation sits at the intersection of ancient rainforest and the vast Pacific Ocean.\n\nSince its founding in 2014, Tofino Yoga has developed deep roots in the local wellness and adventure community. The team brings over 25 years of combined teaching experience and partners with local surf schools, forest guides, and wellness practitioners to create retreat experiences that are distinctly Tofino. This collaborative approach means retreat participants don't just practice yoga; they immerse themselves in the full spectrum of west coast outdoor culture.\n\nThe studio at 1180 Pacific Rim Highway provides a warm, purpose-built practice space that serves as the anchor for all programming. From here, classes and retreat activities extend outward to the area's spectacular natural settings. Beach yoga sessions on Long Beach or Cox Bay offer the soundtrack of ocean waves and the expansive horizon of the open Pacific. Forest practice amid the cathedral-like old-growth cedars and sitka spruce of the surrounding rainforest provides grounding and connection with the ancient energy of the temperate rain coast.\n\nRetreat programming ranges from single-day beach yoga immersions to multi-day residential retreats that combine morning and evening yoga practice with guided nature experiences. Surf and yoga retreats pair morning wave sessions with afternoon practice, creating a dynamic balance of exhilaration and restoration. Wellness retreats may include elements such as forest bathing, tidal pool exploration, wild food foraging, and spa treatments at local wellness centres.\n\nTofino Yoga also offers Yoga Alliance certified teacher training programs that leverage the unique Tofino environment. Training in this setting provides aspiring teachers with the experience of leading outdoor classes, adapting practice to natural settings, and understanding the profound connection between yoga and the natural world.\n\nPrivate yoga sessions and custom group experiences are available for visitors who prefer a personalized approach. The team works with accommodation partners across Tofino to create complete retreat packages that include lodging at a range of price points, from campground cabins to luxury resort suites.\n\nTofino itself adds immeasurably to the retreat experience. The town's year-round surf culture, thriving food scene featuring locally caught seafood and foraged ingredients, Indigenous cultural heritage, and tight-knit community create a destination that inspires visitors long after they leave. The drive to Tofino through Pacific Rim National Park Reserve passes through some of the most spectacular temperate rainforest on the planet.\n\nThe retreat season extends year-round, with summer offering long days and warm beach sessions, and winter bringing dramatic storm-watching opportunities and the introspective energy that accompanies the rain coast's quieter months. Each season brings its own character to the practice and to the Tofino experience.",
