    description:
      "Stowel Lake Farm is a 120-acre organic farm and retreat centre on Salt Spring Island that provides a uniquely grounded setting for yoga and wellness retreats. The farm hosts visiting yoga teachers and retreat organizers throughout the spring, summer, and fall seasons, offering beautiful natural spaces, farm-fresh organic meals, and comfortable accommodation for groups of up to 30 participants. The combination of active organic farming, heritage gardens, forested trails, and lake access creates an environment that naturally supports the contemplative and embodied qualities of yoga retreat practice. Retreat leaders from across British Columbia and beyond choose Stowel Lake Farm for its authentic farm-to-table dining experience, versatile indoor and outdoor practice spaces, and the distinctive Salt Spring Island atmosphere that blends rural tranquility with vibrant arts and culture.",
    long_description:
      "Stowel Lake Farm offers a retreat experience deeply rooted in the land, where the rhythms of organic farming and the seasonal cycles of Salt Spring Island agriculture provide a living backdrop for yoga practice and personal renewal. The 120-acre property encompasses cultivated fields, heritage orchards, native forest, lakefront access, and purpose-built retreat facilities that together create one of British Columbia's most distinctive wellness destinations.\n\nThe farm operates as a retreat venue, welcoming visiting yoga teachers, wellness practitioners, and retreat organizers who bring their programming to the property. This model means that the retreat experience varies depending on the facilitator, but all programs benefit from the farm's exceptional setting, accommodation, and culinary offerings. Regular retreat hosts include some of British Columbia's most respected yoga teachers, offering programs ranging from gentle weekend getaways to intensive week-long immersions.\n\nYoga practice at Stowel Lake Farm takes place in versatile indoor and outdoor spaces. A dedicated studio provides a sheltered practice environment with natural light and views of the surrounding landscape. In warmer months, outdoor practice areas among the gardens and orchards offer the sensory richness of practicing amid growing things, with birdsong, fragrant herbs, and dappled sunlight adding natural dimensions to the experience.\n\nThe farm-to-table dining experience is a highlight of every retreat at Stowel Lake. Meals are prepared using produce grown on the property's organic fields and supplemented by ingredients sourced from neighbouring Salt Spring farms and local waters. The food philosophy emphasizes seasonal eating, whole ingredients, and the understanding that nourishment is an essential component of the retreat experience. Dietary restrictions and preferences are accommodated with care and creativity.\n\nAccommodation options include shared and private rooms in the farm's heritage buildings and purpose-built guest quarters. The rooms are simply appointed with an emphasis on comfort and connection to the surrounding landscape. The absence of unnecessary luxury keeps the focus on the retreat's core purpose of practice, rest, and renewal.\n\nSalt Spring Island provides an ideal context for retreat practice. Known for its artistic community, organic farms, Saturday market, and natural beauty, the island offers ample opportunities for exploration during free time. Hiking trails, beaches, the charming village of Ganges, and local studios and galleries provide enriching diversions that complement the retreat experience.\n\nRetreats at Stowel Lake Farm typically run from late spring through early fall, aligning with the growing season and the finest weather months. Pricing varies by program and facilitator but generally ranges from $1,600 to $3,000 for multi-day retreat packages including accommodation and meals. Individual retreat leaders manage their own registration and pricing, with the farm providing venue and hospitality services.\n\nFor retreat organizers seeking a venue, Stowel Lake Farm offers comprehensive support including accommodation, catering, practice spaces, and logistical assistance. The farm's experienced staff understand the specific needs of yoga retreats and work to ensure that every practical detail supports the program's intentions.",
