    tagline: "Lakeside retreat centre near Vancouver offering serene yoga and wellness getaways in nature",
    description:
      "Loon Lake Lodge & Retreat Centre provides a tranquil lakeside setting for yoga retreats and wellness programs, nestled on the Vancouver side of Golden Ears Provincial Park approximately one hour east of downtown Vancouver. The UBC-affiliated retreat centre offers heated-floor meeting spaces, health-conscious meal planning, and scalable accommodation options that make it suitable for intimate yoga gatherings and larger group retreats alike. The serene lake setting with surrounding mountain forest creates an environment naturally conducive to contemplative practice, while the relative proximity to Metro Vancouver makes it one of the most accessible wilderness retreat destinations in the region. Yoga retreat organizers benefit from professional event support, catering services, and the centre's extensive experience hosting wellness groups. Meals-inclusive rates start from $124 CAD per person per night.",
    long_description:
      "Loon Lake Lodge & Retreat Centre occupies a privileged position in the retreat landscape of Greater Vancouver, offering genuine wilderness immersion within easy driving distance of the city. Located on the shores of Loon Lake within the dramatic mountain scenery of Golden Ears Provincial Park, the centre provides a professional retreat infrastructure in a setting of exceptional natural beauty.\n\nThe centre's affiliation with the University of British Columbia brings institutional quality to its facilities and operations. The lodge features heated-floor meeting and practice spaces designed for comfort during yoga, meditation, and group work. Large windows frame views of the lake and surrounding forest, bringing the natural environment into the practice space. Multiple rooms of varying sizes allow retreat organizers to configure spaces for large group sessions, small group breakouts, and private practice.\n\nAccommodation ranges from comfortable lodge rooms to rustic cabins, providing options at different price points that allow retreat organizers to serve diverse budgets. All accommodation is designed for restful sleep and easy access to the centre's shared facilities and natural surroundings. The lakeside setting means that mornings can begin with mist rising off the water and evenings can conclude with sunset reflections, adding natural beauty to the daily rhythm of retreat life.\n\nMeals at Loon Lake Lodge are prepared by experienced catering staff with attention to health-conscious nutrition. Meal planning can be customized to support the specific dietary needs of yoga retreat groups, including vegetarian, vegan, and allergen-free options. The communal dining experience fosters connection among retreat participants and provides natural transition points in the daily schedule.\n\nThe centre serves primarily as a venue for visiting retreat organizers rather than running its own yoga programming. Yoga teachers and wellness facilitators from across British Columbia book the centre for weekend getaways, week-long intensives, teacher training immersions, and specialized programs. The centre's experienced events team provides logistical support including equipment rental, technology services, and activity coordination.\n\nBeyond yoga practice, the Loon Lake setting offers abundant opportunities for outdoor activities that complement retreat programming. Hiking trails wind through old-growth forest and along mountain ridges within Golden Ears Provincial Park. Canoeing and kayaking on the lake provide contemplative water-based experiences. The surrounding forest offers ideal conditions for walking meditation, forest bathing, and nature photography.\n\nThe centre's proximity to Vancouver, approximately one hour's drive from downtown, makes it exceptionally accessible for retreat participants who may have limited time or prefer not to travel far. This accessibility also makes Loon Lake an ideal venue for day retreats and shorter programs that don't require overnight accommodation.\n\nRates for meals-inclusive overnight stays start from $124 CAD per person per night for adults in shared accommodation, with group discounts available for larger retreat bookings. Complete retreat packages including all meals and two nights of accommodation are available from approximately $999 plus tax per person, depending on the season and accommodation selection.",
